The paper deals with quantum communication complexity, which is a topic in both computer science and quantum information theory. The paper also uses tools from discrepancy theory and information theory, which are subfields of computer science. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also deals with the disjointness problem, which is a well-studied problem in computer science and falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper deals with quantum information complexity, which is a subfield of quantum information theory (cs.QI).
